ATTENTION RSPA FAMILIES: The deadline to apply for
P-EBT food benefits has been extended to July 31. Did your child receive free or reduced-price school meals through the National School Lunch Program during the 2019-2020 school year? If so, your family may be eligible for this one-time food benefit. Visit hhs.texas.gov/pebt to learn more about P-EBT. For questions regarding eligibility or if you need help applying, contact the P-EBT Call Center at 833-613-6220. The public charge rule does not apply to P-EBT benefits.

post_text:
Parents and Staff:

By staying apart for the time being, RSPA is working to ensure that we are limiting the spread of COVID-19 in our community. In service of this, I want to share a one-minute video that reminds us of the most important actions we can take as individuals to reduce risk for ourselves and others:

‚Ä¢ Practice social distancing
‚Ä¢ Wash your hands
‚Ä¢ Stay home as much as you can, especially if you have a cough, fever, or shortness of breath

I encourage you to watch this video with your family. And be sure to share it with family and friends on social media and via email.

Even though we are currently apart, we look forward to coming back together as a community soon.

Best,
Terrell Hutchinson, M. Ed.
Superintendent

#StayHomeStaySafe #TEA #RSPA #ApartWeStandTogether

post_text:
üéâüéâRSPA GOOD THINGS | with Mrs. Brownüéâüéâ
I am Mrs. Brown, 3rd-5th grade lead teacher at RSPA Humble. I hope you are excited for our new learning adventure. Parents, when you made the decision to send your child(ren) to RSPA, we promised an exceptional education.Our current situation does not change anything. We are not just settling for passing out packets of homework and calling it a day. Instead, we are proving our dedication as teachers, we have transitioned from the classroom to virtual learning. We have attended online resource training such as zoom, edpuzzle, and etc. to keep the students engaged as well as academically involved. Our 3-5th graders are so excited that they do not want to leave Zoom at the end of our class. We can really see how much they miss us and miss their classmates. This has truly brought us closer to each other. COVID-19 WILL NOT KEEP US APART.

post_text:
Inclement Weather Alert UPDATE (9.18.19 4:00AM
While the rain has continued, all water reservoirs, streams and creeks are at acceptable levels and there is very little to no street flooding for our area. Therefore, we will hold class as normal today and continue monitoring the weather throughout the day. We will update the website and social media with updates. Please expect transportation delays of up to 10 minutes. If the bus is delayed more than 10 minutes a separate Remind message will be sent.

Thank you.
